fields.slidedescrb1: Discover, Present, Analyze Real-Time Data from Worldwide Sources

fields.question: Where do you get the data?
fields.answer: Universities, governments, and some other web sites.

fields.question: What is the frame rate?
fields.answer: The frame rates, as well as the resolutions, vary based on the cameras.

fields.question: I have cameras. Can I add my cameras to your site?
fields.answer: Not yet. We will add that feature soon.

fields.question: What do you do with the data? Are you tracking where I go?
fields.answer: We do not intend to indentify any individual. Thus, we do not know where you are.

fields.question: If I register, what do you do my data (such as my email address)?
Will you send me any email?
fields.answer: We intend to keep the email traffic low.

fields.question: What do the cameras see?
fields.answer: Most cameras observe traffic or outdoor scenes.

fields.question: Are you recording all data continuously?
Do you retrieve data from password-protected cameras?
fields.answer: Only if the camera owner gives us the password. We will not guess the password of any camera.

fields.name: WebUI
fields.description: Maintain, update and improve the content and user interface at cam2project.net. Build the new website for helps site.

fields.name: Image Database
fields.description: To aggregate all scattered data in a centralized location and add general functionality to it. We want to design a database that can retrieve data(image or video), build index by object detection and store the data and index.

fields.name: Camera Reliability
fields.description: Find factors to identify useful cameras for emergency responses

fields.name: Context-Based Vision
fields.description: Finding a way to incorporate parameters such as location of the camera and time of the image taken into the neural network to improve object detection accuracy of the image.

fields.name: Software Engineering
fields.description: Developing a software engineering process for the all teams in CAM2.

fields.name: Embedded Vision
fields.description: To implement computer vision algorithms such as person re-identification and object tracking on embedded computer systems.

fields.name: Camera Database API and Discovery
fields.description: Ensure easily accessibility of the camera database. To ensure the correctness of data in the database

fields.name: Transfer Learning
fields.description: Provide an effective and time efficient tool that can be used to transfer knowledge across image domain

fields.name: Active Learning
fields.description: Provide relatively improved accuracy by reducing labelled data needed for training

fields.name: Drone Video
fields.description: Develop autonomous solution for a drone to detect doors and handles. We are looking into different approaches: point cloud library(PCL), Tensorflow object-detection API, SIFT & SURF.

fields.name: Forest Inventory Analysis
fields.description: Use optical lens to detect DBH of each tree in a forest

fields.name: Human Behavior
fields.description: To detect and map pedestrian traffic in targeted areas for land development. The data for analysis will be collected through twenty-four hour live feeds.
